Recursion

A function that calls itself is known as a recursive function. And, this technique is known as recursion.

Also, you MUST check this and this to understand and practice recursions perfectly.

Also, you need to define the base cases correctly.

Do you graphically understand how the recursion for Fibonacci works?

Dynamic Programming(DP)

Don't do the same thing twice! That's it.

Steps:

  1. Define the states (sub-problem)
  2. Construct the recurrence
  3. Code the recursion and Memorize everything

Also, the states should not create a cycle. Why?

Iterative vs Recursive

Self-explanatory.

Recursive code for Fibonacci:

#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

const int N = 55;
int f[N];
bool is_computed[N];
int fibo(int i) {
  if (i == 0) return 0;
  if (i == 1) return 1;
  if (is_computed[i]) return f[i];
  f[i] = fibo(i - 1) + fibo(i - 2);
  is_computed[i] = true;
  return f[i];
}
int32_t main() {
  ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  cin.tie(0);
  cout << fibo(50) << '\n';
  return 0;
}

Iterative code for Fibonacci:

#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

const int N = 55;
int f[N];
int32_t main() {
  ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  cin.tie(0);
  f[0] = 0;
  f[1] = 1;
  int n = 5;
  for (int i = 2; i <= n; i++) {
    f[i] = f[i - 1] + f[i - 2];
  }
  cout << f[n] << '\n';
  return 0;
}

[Problem 1]Minimum Steps to Reach 1

You are given an integer n(1≤n≤105)n(1 \le n \le 10^5)n(1≤n≤105). You can perform the following operations on it(as many as times as you want).

  1. Subtract 111 from it. (assign n:=n−1n := n - 1n:=n−1)
  2. If its divisible by 222, divide by 222. (if nmod  2==0n \mod 2 == 0nmod2==0 , then assign n:=n/2n := n / 2n:=n/2)
  3. If its divisible by 333, divide by 333. (if nmod  3==0n \mod 3 == 0nmod3==0 , then assign n:=n/3n := n / 3n:=n/3).

Find the minimum number of operations to make n=1n = 1n=1.

Example: For n=7n = 7n=7 , output: 3(7−1=6/3=2/2=1)3 (7 -1 = 6 /3 = 2 /2 = 1)3(7−1=6/3=2/2=1)

What is your solution for this? Does greedy work?

Step 1: Define the sub-problem
dpi=dp_i =dpi​= minimum steps to reach 111 from iii

Step 2: Construct the recurrence
dpi=1+min⁡(dpi−1,dpi/2dp_i = 1 + \min(dp_{i - 1}, dp_{i / 2}dpi​=1+min(dpi−1​,dpi/2​ if imod  2==0,dpi/3i \mod 2 == 0, dp_{i / 3}imod2==0,dpi/3​ if imod  3==0)i \mod 3 == 0)imod3==0)

Step 3: Code the recursion and Memorize everything

#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

const int N = 1e5 + 9;
int step[N];
int min_steps(int i) {
  if (i == 1) return 0;
  if (step[i] != -1) return step[i];
  int ans = min_steps(i - 1) + 1;
  if (i % 2 == 0) {
    ans = min(ans, min_steps(i / 2) + 1);
  }
  if (i % 3 == 0) {
    ans = min(ans, min_steps(i / 3) + 1);
  }
  step[i] = ans;
  return step[i];
}
int32_t main() {
  ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  cin.tie(0);
  memset(step, -1, sizeof step);
  int n = 10;
  cout << min_steps(n) << '\n';
  return 0;
}

Note that defining the sub-problems is not that easy. It gets easier if you solve more problems. There is literally no other way.

[Problem 2]Number of ways

You are given an integer n(1≤n≤105)n(1 \le n \le 10^5)n(1≤n≤105). Find the number of ways to write nnn as sums of 111 and 333. Output the answer modulo 109+710^9+7109+7.

Example: For n=4n = 4n=4, output: 3(1+1+1+1,1+3,3+1)3(1 + 1 + 1 + 1,1 + 3, 3 + 1)3(1+1+1+1,1+3,3+1)

Can you solve it in O(n)O(n)O(n)?

Recursive Code:

#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

const int N = 1e5 + 9, mod = 1e9 + 7;
int ways[N];
int count(int i) {
  if (i == 1) return 1;
  if (i == 2) return 1;
  if (i == 3) return 2;
  if (ways[i] != -1) return ways[i];
  return ways[i] = (count(i - 1) + count(i - 3)) % mod;
}
int32_t main() {
  ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  cin.tie(0);
  memset(ways, -1, sizeof ways);
  cout << count(100000) << '\n';
  return 0;
}

Iterative Code:

#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

const int N = 1e5 + 9;
int step[N];
int32_t main() {
  ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  cin.tie(0);
  int n = 100000;
  step[1] = 0;
  for (int i = 2; i <= n; i++) {
    int ans = step[i - 1] + 1;
    if (i % 2 == 0) {
      ans = min(ans, step[i / 2] + 1);
    }
    if (i % 3 == 0) {
      ans = min(ans, step[i / 3] + 1);
    }
    step[i] = ans;
  }
  cout << step[n] << '\n';
  return 0;
}

[Problem 3]Number of Ways 2

You are given an integer n(1≤n≤1000)n(1 \le n \le 1000)n(1≤n≤1000). Find the number of ways to write nnn as sums of positive integers. Output the answer modulo 109+710^9+7109+7.

Example: For n=3n = 3n=3, output: 4(1+1+1,1+2,2+1,3)4(1 + 1 + 1, 1 + 2, 2 + 1, 3)4(1+1+1,1+2,2+1,3)

Can you solve it in O(n2)O(n^2)O(n2)?

#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

const int N = 1e3 + 9, mod = 1e9 + 7;
int ways[N];
int count(int n) {
  if (n == 0) return 1;
  if (ways[n] != -1) return ways[n];
  int ans = 0;
  for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
    ans += count(n - i);
    ans %= mod;
  }
  return ways[n] = ans;
}
int32_t main() {
  ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  cin.tie(0);
  memset(ways, -1, sizeof ways);
  cout << count(4) << '\n';
  return 0;
}

[Problem 4]0/1 Knapsack

Problem: link

Tutorial: link

#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

const int N = 105;
#define int long long
int n, W, w[N], v[N], dp[N][100005];
int rec(int i, int weight) {
  if (i == n + 1) return 0;
  if (dp[i][weight] != -1) return dp[i][weight];
  int ans = rec(i + 1, weight);
  if (weight + w[i] <= W) ans = max(ans, rec(i + 1, weight + w[i]) + v[i]);
  return dp[i][weight] = ans;
}
int32_t main() {
  ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  cin.tie(0);
  cin >> n >> W;
  for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
    cin >> w[i] >> v[i];
  }
  memset(dp, -1, sizeof dp);
  cout << rec(1, 0) << '\n';
  return 0;
}

[Problem 5]DP on Matrix

Problem: Given a cost matrix Cost[][] of size n×mn \times mn×m where Cost[i][j] denotes the Cost of visiting cell with coordinates (i,j), find a min-cost path to reach the cell (n,m) from the cell (1,1) under the condition that you can only travel one step right or one step down. (We assume that all costs are positive integers)

#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

int n, m, a[10][10], inf = 1e9 + 7;
int dp[10][10];
int min_cost(int i, int j) {
  if (j > m or i > n) return inf;
  if (i == n and j == m) return a[i][j];
  if (dp[i][j] != -1) return dp[i][j];
  return dp[i][j] = a[i][j] + min(min_cost(i + 1, j), min_cost(i, j + 1));
}
void path(int i, int j) {
  cout << "(" << i << ", " << j << ") -> ";
  if (i == n and j == m) return;
  int right = min_cost(i, j + 1);
  int down = min_cost(i + 1, j);
  if (right <= down) {
    path(i, j + 1);
  }
  else {
    path(i + 1, j);
  }
}
int32_t main() {
  ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  cin.tie(0);
  cin >> n >> m;
  for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
    for (int j = 1; j <= m; j++) {
      cin >> a[i][j];
    }
  }
  memset(dp, -1, sizeof dp);
  cout << min_cost(1, 1) << '\n';
  path(1, 1);
  return 0;
}

[Problem 6]DP on Acyclic Graphs (Easy Version)

Problem: link

Caution: If there is a cycle, then it is not possible to do DP

#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

const int N = 1e5 + 9;
int dp[N];
vector<int> g[N];
int rec(int u) {
  if (dp[u] != -1) return dp[u];
  int ans = 0;
  for (auto v: g[u]) {
    ans = max(ans, 1 + rec(v));
  }
  return dp[u] = ans;
}
int32_t main() {
  ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  cin.tie(0);
  int n, m; cin >> n >> m;
  while (m--) {
    int u, v; cin >> u >> v;
    g[u].push_back(v);
  }
  memset(dp, -1, sizeof dp);
  int ans = 0;
  for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
    ans = max(ans, rec(i));
  }
  cout << ans << '\n';
  return 0;
}

[Problem 7]Dp on Tree (Easy Version)

Problem 1: Given a rooted tree with nnn nodes. Find the sizes of all substrees in O(n)O(n)O(n).

#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

const int N = 1e5 + 9;
int sz[N];
vector<int> g[N];
void dfs(int u, int p) {
  sz[u] = 1;
  for (auto v: g[u]) {
    if (v != p) {
      dfs(v, u);
      sz[u] += sz[v];
    }
  }
}
int32_t main() {
  ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  cin.tie(0);
  int n; cin >> n;
  for (int i = 1; i < n; i++) {
    int u, v; cin >> u >> v;
    g[u].push_back(v);
    g[v].push_back(u);
  }
  dfs(1, 0);
  for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
    cout << sz[i] << ' ';
  }
  return 0;
}

Problem 2: link

#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

const int N = 1e5 + 9, mod = 1e9 + 7;
int dp[N][2];
vector<int> g[N];
void dfs(int u, int p) {
  dp[u][0] = 1;
  dp[u][1] = 1;
  for (auto v: g[u]) {
    if (v != p) {
      dfs(v, u);
      dp[u][0] = 1LL * dp[u][0] * (dp[v][0] + dp[v][1]) % mod;
      dp[u][1] = 1LL * dp[u][1] * dp[v][0] % mod;
    }
  }
}
int32_t main() {
  ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  cin.tie(0);
  int n; cin >> n;
  for (int i = 1; i < n; i++) {
    int u, v; cin >> u >> v;
    g[u].push_back(v);
    g[v].push_back(u);
  }
  dfs(1, 0);
  cout << (dp[1][0] + dp[1][1]) % mod << '\n';
  return 0;
}

[Problem 8]Longest Common Subsequence(LCS)

Problem: link

Tutorial: link

#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

const int N = 3030;
string a, b;
int dp[N][N];
int lcs(int i, int j) {
  if (i >= a.size() or j >= b.size()) return 0;
  if (dp[i][j] != -1) return dp[i][j];
  int ans = lcs(i + 1, j);
  ans = max(ans, lcs(i, j + 1));
  if (a[i] == b[j]) {
    ans = max(ans, lcs(i + 1, j + 1) + 1);
  }
  return dp[i][j] = ans;
}
void print(int i, int j) {
  if (i >= a.size() or j >= b.size()) return;
  if (a[i] == b[j]) {
    cout << a[i];
    print(i + 1, j + 1);
    return;
  }
  int x = lcs(i + 1, j);
  int y = lcs(i, j + 1);
  if (x >= y) {
    print(i + 1, j);
  }
  else {
    print(i, j + 1);
  }
}
int32_t main() {
  ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  cin.tie(0);
  cin >> a >> b;
  memset(dp, -1, sizeof dp);
  // cout << lcs(0, 0) << '\n';
  print(0, 0);
  return 0;
}

[Problem 9] Longest Increasing Subsequence(LIS)

Problem and Tutorial: link

How to solve it in O(n2)O(n^2)O(n2)?

#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

const int N = 10010;
int a[N], dp[N];
int32_t main() {
  ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  cin.tie(0);
  int n; cin >> n;
  for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
    cin >> a[i];
  }
  for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
    dp[i] = 1;
    for (int j = 1; j < i; j++) {
      if (a[j] < a[i]) {
        dp[i] = max(dp[i], dp[j] + 1);
      }
    }
  }
  int ans = 0;
  for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
    ans = max(ans, dp[i]);
  }
  cout << ans << '\n';
  return 0;
}

[Problem 10]Do we need all the states?

Problem: link

#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

const int N = 3001;
double dp[N][N], p[N];
bool vis[N][N];
int n;
double rec(int i, int head, int tail) {
  if (i == n + 1) {
    if (head > tail) return 1;
    else return 0;
  }
  if (vis[i][head]) return dp[i][head];
  vis[i][head] = true;
  double ans = p[i] * rec(i + 1, head + 1, tail);
  ans += (1 - p[i]) * rec(i + 1, head, tail + 1);
  return dp[i][head] = ans;
}
int32_t main() {
  ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  cin.tie(0);
  cin >> n;
  for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
    cin >> p[i];
  }
  cout << fixed << setprecision(10) << rec(1, 0, 0) << '\n';
  return 0;
}

Memory Optimization and Recursive to Iterative

Steps:

  1. Construct iterative DP with bad space complexity
  2. Optimize it

Problem: link

Recursive:

#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

const int N = 105, X = 1e6 + 9, inf = 1e9;
int n, x, a[N];
int dp[N][X];
int rec(int i, int sum) {
  if (sum > x) return inf;
  if (i == n + 1) {
    if (sum == x) return 0;
    return inf;
  }
  if (dp[i][sum] != -1) return dp[i][sum];
  int ans = rec(i + 1, sum);
  ans = min(ans, 1 + rec(i, sum + a[i]));
  return dp[i][sum] = ans;
}
int32_t main() {
  ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  cin.tie(0);
  cin >> n >> x;
  for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
    cin >> a[i];
  }
  memset(dp, -1, sizeof dp);
  int ans = rec(1, 0);
  cout << (ans >= inf ? -1 : ans) << '\n';
  return 0;
}

Iterative:

#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

const int N = 105, X = 1e6 + 9, inf = 1e9;
int n, x, a[N];
int dp[N][X];
int32_t main() {
  ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  cin.tie(0);
  cin >> n >> x;
  for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
    cin >> a[i];
  }
  dp[0][0] = 0;
  for (int sum = 1; sum <= x; sum++) {
    dp[0][sum] = inf;
  }
  for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
    for (int sum = 0; sum <= x; sum++) {
      dp[i][sum] = dp[i - 1][sum];
      if (sum >= a[i]) dp[i][sum] = min(dp[i][sum], dp[i][sum - a[i]] + 1);
    }
  }
  cout << (dp[n][x] >= inf ? -1 : dp[n][x]) << '\n';
  return 0;
}

Memory Optimized:

#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

const int N = 105, X = 1e6 + 9, inf = 1e9;
int n, x, a[N];
int dp[2][X];
int32_t main() {
  ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  cin.tie(0);
  cin >> n >> x;
  for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
    cin >> a[i];
  }
  dp[0][0] = 0;
  for (int sum = 1; sum <= x; sum++) {
    dp[0][sum] = inf;
  }
  for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
    for (int sum = 0; sum <= x; sum++) {
      dp[1][sum] = dp[0][sum];
      if (sum >= a[i]) dp[1][sum] = min(dp[1][sum], dp[1][sum - a[i]] + 1);
    }
    for (int sum = 0; sum <= x; sum++) {
      dp[0][sum] = dp[1][sum];
    }
  }
  cout << (dp[1][x] >= inf ? -1 : dp[1][x]) << '\n';
  return 0;
}

Coordinate Compression and DP Optimization

Steps:

  1. Construct iterative DP with bad complexity
  2. Optimize it

How to solve LIS in O(nlog⁡n)O(n \log n)O(nlogn)?

#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

const int N = 2e5 + 9, M = 2e5 + 9;

struct ST {
  int t[4 * M];
  static const int inf = 1e9;
  ST() {
    memset(t, 0, sizeof t);
  }
  void upd(int n, int b, int e, int i, int x) {
    if (b > i || e < i) return;
    if (b == e && b == i) {
      t[n] = max(t[n], x);
      return;
    }
    int mid = (b + e) >> 1, l = n << 1, r = l | 1;
    upd(l, b, mid, i, x);
    upd(r, mid + 1, e, i, x);
    t[n] = max(t[l], t[r]);
  }
  int query(int n, int b, int e, int i, int j) {
    if (b > j || e < i) return -inf;
    if (b >= i && e <= j) return t[n];
    int mid = (b + e) >> 1, l = n << 1, r = l | 1;
    int L = query(l, b, mid, i, j);
    int R = query(r, mid + 1, e, i, j);
    return max(L, R);
  }
}t;
int a[N], dp[N];
int32_t main() {
  ios_base::sync_with_stdio(0);
  cin.tie(0);
  int n; cin >> n;
  set<int> se;
  for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
    cin >> a[i];
    se.insert(a[i]);
  }
  map<int, int> mp;
  int id = 0;
  for (auto x: se) {
    mp[x] = ++id;
  }
  for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
    a[i] = mp[a[i]]; // coordinate compression, now all a[i] are 1 <= a[i] <= n which is cute
  }
  for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
    dp[i] = 1;
    // int mx = 0;
    // for (int j = 1; j < i; j++) {
    //   if (a[j] < a[i]) {
    //     mx = max(mx, dp[j]);
    //   }
    // }
    // optimized the loop
    if (a[i] != 1) {
      int mx = t.query(1, 1, M, 1, a[i] - 1);
      mx++;
      dp[i] = max(dp[i], mx);
    }
    t.upd(1, 1, M, a[i], dp[i]);
  }
  int ans = 0;
  for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
    ans = max(ans, dp[i]);
  }
  cout << ans << '\n';
  return 0;
}

1. Problem A

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

int32_t main() {
    ios_base::sync_with_stdio(false); cin.tie(NULL);
    int n;
    cin >> n;
    vector<int> h(n);
    for(auto &x: h) cin >> x;
    int dp[n];
    for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) dp[i] = INT_MAX;
    dp[0] = 0;
    for(int i = 0; i < n - 1; i++) {

    }

return 0;
}

10. Problem J

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

#define int long long
const int N = 3000 + 5;

int a[N];
pair<int, int> dp[N][N];
int n;

pair<int, int> wtf(int i, int j, int k) {
    if(i >= n || j < 0 || i > j) return {0, 0};
    if(dp[i][j] != make_pair(-1LL, -1LL)) return dp[i][j];
    pair<int, int> ans;
    if(k == 0) {
        auto tmp1 = wtf(i + 1, j, 1);
        int x1 = a[i] + tmp1.first;
        int y1 = tmp1.second;

        auto tmp2 = wtf(i, j - 1, 1);
        int x2 = a[j] + tmp2.first;
        int y2 = tmp2.second;

        if(x2 - y2 > x1 - y1) {
            ans = {x2, y2};
        }
        else {
            ans = {x1, y1};
        }
    }
    else {
        auto tmp1 = wtf(i + 1, j, 0);
        int x1 = tmp1.first;
        int y1 = a[i] + tmp1.second;

        auto tmp2 = wtf(i, j - 1, 0);
        int x2 = tmp2.first;
        int y2 = a[j] + tmp2.second;

        if(x2 - y2 < x1 - y1) {
            ans = {x2, y2};
        }
        else {
            ans = {x1, y1};
        }
    }
    return dp[i][j] = ans;
}

int32_t main() {
    ios_base::sync_with_stdio(false); cin.tie(NULL);
    cin >> n;
    for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) cin >> a[i];
    memset(dp, -1, sizeof dp);
    auto tmp = wtf(0, n - 1, 0);
    cout << tmp.first - tmp.second << '\n';

return 0;
}

#define int long long
const int N = 400 + 5;

int a[N];
pair<int, int> dp[N][N];

pair<int, int> min_combine(int l, int r) {
    if(dp[l][r] != make_pair(-1LL, -1LL)) return dp[l][r];
    if(l == r) {
        return {0, a[l]};
    }
    pair<int, int> ans = {LLONG_MAX, LLONG_MAX};
    for(int m = l; m < r; m++) {
        auto x = min_combine(l, m), y = min_combine(m + 1, r);
        ans = min(ans, {x.first + y.first + x.second + y.second, x.second + y.second});
    }
    return dp[l][r] = ans;
}

            dp[i][j] = {-1, -1};
        }
    }
    for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        cin >> a[i];
    }
    cout << min_combine(0, n - 1).first << '\n';

return 0;
}

13. Problem M

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

#define int long long

const int mod = 1e9 + 7;
const int N = 100000 + 10;

vector<int> G[N];
bool vis[N];
pair<int, int> dfs(int u, int par) {
    vis[u] = true;
    if(G[u].size() == 0) return {1, 1};
    if(u != par && G[u].size() == 1) {
        return {1, 1};
    }
    pair<int, int> ans = {1, 1};
    for(auto v: G[u]) {
        if(!vis[v] && v != par) {
            auto p = dfs(v, u);
            ans.first *= p.second;
            ans.first %= mod;
            ans.second *= ((p.first + p.second) % mod);
            ans.second %= mod;
        }
    }
    return ans;
}

    int n;
    cin >> n;
    for(int i = 1; i < n; i++) {
        int x, y;
        cin >> x >> y;
        G[x].push_back(y);
        G[y].push_back(x);
    }
    auto ans = dfs(1, 1);
    cout << (ans.first + ans.second) % mod << '\n';
return 0;
}

14. Problem N

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

#define int long long
const int N = 2e5 + 10;
int h[N], a[N];

struct ST {
    #define lc (n << 1)
    #define rc ((n << 1) + 1)
    int t[4 * N];
    ST() {
        memset(t, 0, sizeof t);
    }
    inline void pull(int n) {
        t[n] = max(t[lc], t[rc]);  
    }
    inline int combine(int a, int b) {
        return max(a, b);
    }
    void upd(int n, int b, int e, int i, int x) {
        if(b > i || e < i) return;
        if(b == e && b == i) {
            t[n] = max(t[n], x);
            return;
        }
        int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
        upd(lc, b, mid, i, x);
        upd(rc, mid + 1, e, i, x);
        pull(n);
    }
    int query(int n, int b, int e, int i, int j) {
        if(b > j || e < i) return 0;
        if(b >= i && e <= j) return t[n];
        int mid = (b + e) >> 1;
        return combine(query(lc, b, mid, i, j), query(rc, mid + 1, e, i, j)); 
    }
}t;

int32_t main() {
    ios_base::sync_with_stdio(false); cin.tie(NULL);
    int n;
    cin >> n;
    for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        cin >> h[i];
    }   
    for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        cin >> a[i];
    }
    int dp[n];
    dp[0] = a[0];
    t.upd(1, 1, N, h[0], dp[0]);
    for(int i = 1; i < n; i++) {
        int mx = t.query(1, 1, N, 1, h[i] - 1);
        dp[i] = mx + a[i];
        t.upd(1, 1, N, h[i], dp[i]);
    }
    cout << *max_element(dp, dp + n) << '\n';

return 0;
}

string a, b, c;
int sa, sb, sc;

int lcs(int x, int y, int z) {
    if(x >= sa or y >= sb or z >= sc) return 0;
    if(dp[x][y][z] != -1) return dp[x][y][z];
    if(a[x] == b[y] && b[y] == c[z]) {
        return dp[x][y][z] = 1 + lcs(x + 1, y + 1, z + 1);
    }
    return dp[x][y][z] = max({lcs(x + 1, y, z), lcs(x, y + 1, z), lcs(x, y, z + 1)});
}

int32_t main() {
    ios_base::sync_with_stdio(false); cin.tie(NULL);

    int t;
    cin >> t;
    for(int cs = 1; cs <= t; cs++) {
        cin >> a >> b >> c;
        sa = a.size(), sb = b.size(), sc = c.size();
        memset(dp, -1, sizeof dp);
        cout << "Case " << cs << ": ";
        cout << lcs(0, 0, 0) << '\n';
    }

return 0;
}

21. Problem U

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

const int INF = 1e9 + 10;

void max_self(int& a, int b) {
    a = max(a, b);
}

int32_t main() {
    ios_base::sync_with_stdio(false); cin.tie(NULL);
    int t;
    cin >> t;
    for(int cs = 1; cs <= t; cs++) {
        int n;
        cin >> n;
        vector<int> s(n);
        for(auto &x: s) cin >> x;
        int dp[n][2];
        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            dp[i][0] = dp[i][1] = -INF;
        }
        dp[1][0] = s[0];
        for(int i = 2; i < n; i++) {
            max_self(dp[i][0], max(dp[i - 1][0], dp[i - 1][1]));
            max_self(dp[i][1], s[i] + dp[i - 1][0]);
        }
        int ans = dp[n - 1][0];
        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            dp[i][0] = dp[i][1] = -INF;
        }
        dp[1][1] = s[1], dp[1][0] = 0;
        for(int i = 2; i < n; i++) {
            max_self(dp[i][0], max(dp[i - 1][0], dp[i - 1][1]));
            max_self(dp[i][1], s[i] + dp[i - 1][0]);
        }
        max_self(ans, max(dp[n - 1][1], dp[n - 1][0]));
        cout << "Case " << cs << ": ";
        cout << ans << '\n';
    }
return 0;
}

23. Problem W

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

#define int long long

int32_t main() {
    ios_base::sync_with_stdio(false); cin.tie(NULL);
    
    int n;
    cin >> n;
    int a[n];
    int psum[n];
    for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        cin >> a[i];
        psum[i] = a[i];
        if(i > 0) psum[i] += psum[i - 1];
    }
    int tsum = psum[n - 1];
    if(tsum % 3) {
        cout << 0 << '\n';
        return 0;
    }
    int sum = tsum / 3;
    int ans = 0;
    int sum2 = 0;
    for(int i = n - 2; i >= 0; i--) {
        if(psum[i] == sum) {
            ans += sum2;
        }
        if(psum[i] == 2 * sum) {
            sum2++;
        }
    }
    cout << ans << '\n';

return 0;
}

24. Problem X

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

const int N = 1000 + 5;
string s;
int dp[N][N];

int max_palindrome(int x, int y) {
    if(x > y) return 0;
    if(dp[x][y] != -1) return dp[x][y];
    int ans = 0;
    if(s[x] == s[y]) {
        if(x != y) ans = 2;
        else ans = 1;
        ans += max_palindrome(x + 1, y - 1);
    }
    ans = max(ans, max_palindrome(x + 1, y));
    ans = max(ans, max_palindrome(x, y - 1));
    return dp[x][y] = ans;
}

int32_t main() {
    ios_base::sync_with_stdio(false); cin.tie(NULL);
    int t;
    cin >> t;
    getline(cin, s);
    while(t--) {
        memset(dp, -1, sizeof dp);
        getline(cin, s);
        int n = s.size();
        cout << max_palindrome(0, n - 1) << '\n';
    }

return 0;
}

CSES 1637: Removing Digits

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

const int N = 1e6 + 10, inf = 1e9;

int dp[N];

int min_steps(int x) {
    if(x == 0) return 0;
    if(dp[x] != -1) return dp[x];
    int ans = inf;
    int xx = x;
    while(xx > 0) {
        if(xx % 10 != 0)
            ans = min(ans, 1 + min_steps(x - (xx % 10)));
        xx /= 10;
    }
    return dp[x] = ans;
}

int32_t main() {
    ios_base::sync_with_stdio(false); cin.tie(NULL);
    
    int n;
    cin >> n;
    memset(dp, -1, sizeof dp);
    cout << min_steps(n) << '\n';

return 0;
}

CSES 1639: Edit Distance

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

const int N = 5000 + 5;

string a, b;
int dp[N][N], sa, sb;

int min_changes(int i, int j) {
    if(i == sa) return sb - j;
    if(j == sb) return sa - i;
    if(dp[i][j] != -1) return dp[i][j];
    int ans = !(a[i] == b[j]) + min_changes(i + 1, j + 1);
    ans = min(ans, 1 + min_changes(i, j + 1));
    ans = min(ans, 1 + min_changes(i + 1, j));
    return dp[i][j] = ans;
}

int32_t main() {
    ios_base::sync_with_stdio(false); cin.tie(NULL);
    cin >> a >> b;
    sa = a.size(), sb = b.size();
    memset(dp, -1, sizeof dp);
    cout << min_changes(0, 0) << '\n';

return 0;
}

CSES 1638: Grid Paths

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

const int mod = 1e9 + 7;

int32_t main() {
    ios_base::sync_with_stdio(false); cin.tie(NULL);
    
    int n;
    cin >> n;
    int a[n][n];
    memset(a, 0, sizeof a);
    char ch;
    for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        for(int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
            cin >> ch;
            if(ch == '.') a[i][j] = 1;
        }
    }
    int dp[n][n];
    memset(dp, 0, sizeof dp);
    dp[n - 1][n - 1] = a[n - 1][n - 1];
    for(int i = n - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
        for(int j = n - 1; j >= 0; j--) {
            if(a[i][j]) {
                if(i + 1 < n) {
                    dp[i][j] += dp[i + 1][j];
                    dp[i][j] %= mod;
                }
                if(j + 1 < n) {
                    dp[i][j] += dp[i][j + 1];
                    dp[i][j] %= mod;
                }
            }
        }
    }
    cout << dp[0][0] << '\n';

return 0;
}

CSES 1634: Minimizing Coins

Editorial: link

using namespace std;

const int inf = 1e9;

int32_t main() {
    ios_base::sync_with_stdio(false); cin.tie(NULL);
    
    int n, x;
    cin >> n >> x;
    int dp[x + 1], a[n];
    for(int i = 0; i <= x; i++) {
        dp[i] = inf;
    }
    dp[0] = 0;
    for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        cin >> a[i];
    }
    for(int i = 0; i <= x; i++) {
        for(int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
            if(a[j] <= i)
                dp[i] = min(dp[i], dp[i - a[j]] + 1);
        }
    }
    cout << (dp[x] == inf ? -1 : dp[x]) << '\n';

return 0;
}

CSES 1745: Money Sums

using namespace std;

    ios_base::sync_with_stdio(false); cin.tie(NULL);
    
    int n;
    cin >> n;
    int a[n];
    int sum = 0;
    for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        cin >> a[i];
        sum += a[i];
    }
    int dp[sum + 1] = {0};
    dp[0] = 1;
    
    for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        for(int j = sum; j >= a[i]; j--) {
            dp[j] |= dp[j - a[i]];
        }
    }
    cout << accumulate(dp, dp + sum, 0) << '\n';
    for(int i = 1; i <= sum; i++) {
        if(dp[i]) cout << i << ' ';
    }
    cout << '\n';
return 0;
}

CSES 1746: Array Description

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

const int N = 1e5 + 10, mod = 1e9 + 7;

int n, m, a[N], dp[N][105];

int yo(int x, int v) {
    if(x == n - 1) {
        if(a[x] == 0) return 1;
        else return v == a[x];
    }
    if(dp[x][v] != -1) return dp[x][v];
    if(a[x] != 0) {
        if(a[x] != v) return dp[x][v] = 0;
    }
    dp[x][v] = yo(x + 1, v);
    if(v + 1 <= m) {
        dp[x][v] += yo(x + 1, v + 1);
        dp[x][v] %= mod;
    }
    if(v - 1 >= 1) {
        dp[x][v] += yo(x + 1, v - 1);
        dp[x][v] %= mod;
    }
    return dp[x][v];
}

int32_t main() {
    ios_base::sync_with_stdio(false); cin.tie(NULL);
    
    cin >> n >> m;
    for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        cin >> a[i];
    }
    memset(dp, -1, sizeof dp);
    int ans = 0;
    if(a[0] == 0) {
        for(int i = 1; i <= m; i++) {
            ans += yo(0, i);
            ans %= mod;
        }
    }
    else {
        ans = yo(0, a[0]);
    }
    cout << ans << '\n';

return 0;
}

CSES 1093: Two Sets II

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

const int N = 500 + 5, mod = 1e9 + 7;
int dp[N][125255];
int tg, n;

int yo(int i, int s) {
    if(s == tg) return 1;
    if(i == n) return 0;
    if(dp[i][s] != -1) return dp[i][s];
    return dp[i][s] = (yo(i + 1, s + i) + yo(i + 1, s)) % mod;
}

int32_t main() {
    ios_base::sync_with_stdio(false); cin.tie(NULL);
    
    cin >> n;
    int sum = (n * (n + 1)) / 2;
    if(sum & 1) {
        cout << 0 << '\n';
        return 0;
    }
    tg = sum / 2;
    memset(dp, -1, sizeof dp);
    cout << yo(1, 0) << '\n';

return 0;
}

CSES 1140: Projects

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

#define int long long

int32_t main() {
    ios_base::sync_with_stdio(false); cin.tie(NULL);

    int n;
    cin >> n;
    int a[n], b[n], p[n];
    map<int, int> mp;
    vector<int> vt;
    for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        cin >> a[i] >> b[i] >> p[i];
        vt.push_back(a[i]);
        vt.push_back(b[i]);
    }
    sort(vt.begin(), vt.end());
    int cnt = 0;
    for(auto x: vt) {
        if(mp[x] == 0) mp[x] = ++cnt;
    }
    vector<vector<pair<int, int>>> d;
    d.resize(cnt + 1);
    for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        d[mp[a[i]]].push_back({mp[b[i]], p[i]});
    }
    int ct = 0;
    int dp[cnt + 2] = {0};
    for(int i = cnt; i >= 1; i--) {
        dp[i] = max(dp[i], dp[i + 1]);
        for(auto j: d[i]) {
            ct++;
            dp[i] = max(dp[i], j.second + dp[j.first + 1]);
        }
    }
    cout << dp[1] << '\n';

return 0;
}

CSES 1097: Removal Game

Editorial: link

Code(C++) 
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;
 
#define int long long
 
const int N = 5e3 + 5;
 
int n, a[N], dp[N][N];

int give_max(int x, int y) {
    if(x > y) return 0;
    if(dp[x][y] != -1) return dp[x][y];
    return dp[x][y] = max(a[x] - give_max(x + 1, y), a[y] - give_max(x, y - 1));
}
 
int32_t main() {
    ios_base::sync_with_stdio(false); cin.tie(NULL);
    
    cin >> n;
    for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        cin >> a[i];
    }
    memset(dp, -1, sizeof dp);
    int max_diff = give_max(0, n - 1);
    cout << (accumulate(a, a + n, 0LL) + max_diff) / 2 << '\n';
 
return 0;
}
